metadata.name: Perspective #32
metadata.description:
A few primitives and a lot of points.

Warning: This piece is GPU intensive, it may not render on lower end devices.

Keys
s: Take a screenshot
space: Pause/Play the animation.
r: Play a new animation
↑: Increase point alpha
↓: Decrease point alpha
→: Increase point density
←: Decrease point density

URL Params
w: Width of the canvas - (ex, w=1024) - [0-2048]
h: Height of the canvas - (ex, h=1024) - [0-2048]
a: To set the alpha for the points - [0.0-1.0]
p: To set the total number of points to draw (in millions) [1-8]
s: Make the visual static - (ex, s=1)

metadata.name: Obscure Archive #120
metadata.description:
Tabula rasa - we are all born without mental condition built-in, therefore knowledge and emotions come from experience.

As we grow up, emotions and feelings come to us naturally. Joy, sadness, anger, tranquility, confusion - to name a few, all these emotions makes us who we are today consciously or subconsciously. Yet, negative emotions are easier to remember and sticks longer compared to the positive ones.

Though, some people are lucky enough to be able to express their emotions freely to their surrounding, letting others know what they're feeling & what they've been through. While some other finds it harder to let go of those negative emotions. Wanting them to be gone but, alas, they can't find the right conditions to do so. Or even worse, these emotions get mixed up and tangled with their thoughts and memories making it harder to read or express.

__________

Obscure Archive is trying to capture what I (or maybe, you too) have been feeling constantly. These negative emotions is expressed and written as the text within the artwork, with the supergraphic representing thoughts & memories that we have. Some of the artwork has no overlay, just like those who can express their emotions freely. While some other have a completely different overlay, with messy text and supergraphic representing the concealment & entangled thoughts that make the emotions harder to read.

__________

made with ❤️ and p5js

metadata.name: A Slight Case of Overbombing #194
metadata.description:
Inspired by monochromatic art of the late 60s, Russian folk-art woodblock prints, and the stylised colours of British underground comics, excited to introduce a series of bold rich landscapes. England, Wales, Ireland and Scotland represented by red, yellow, green and blue, sometimes a house or two, and groovy clouds.

Instructions ::

.     - speed up
,     - slow down
space - pause
n     - toggle noise
p     - cycle palette
h     - toggle high-res (and definitely intentional pixel shift)
s     - download and save image

metadata.name: 0xFoif #159
metadata.description:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
NOTE TO COLLECTORS:

This token will be sold as a Dutch auction. Every 5 minutes, the price will change based on the following schedule:
20 / 15 / 10 / 5 / 2 tez

After that, the price will remain fixed at 2 tez.
If there are tokens remaining after 72 hours, they will be burnt.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

0xFoif

Inspired by Tyler Hobbs' water color studies and the splitting algorithm of 0xDrue, 0xFoif is a collection of interplay between a strong grid with clear cut splits and a blurriness introduced by multiple transparent layers.

Zürich/Quito, January 2022
❤️ pifragile

metadata.name: GE-I #113
metadata.description:
The first in a series of grid experiments.

Made of simple expressions of shape, color, and layout. There are 10 features including 32 pallets & 34 shape sets. The base grid is constructed of either 2x2, 4x4, 6x6, 8x8, or 20x20 layouts.
